22/12/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH Defence Minister Nikola Radovanovic met with Macedonian counterpart Lazar Elenovski in Sarajevo on Thursday (December 21st), discussing ways to boost military co-operation.
Elenovski vowed to assist BiH in meeting its obligations to NATO's Partnership for Peace (PfP) programme.
Radovanovic conceded that the PfP invitation last month was a surprise for BiH.
On Friday, Elenovski was in Podgorica to meet with Montenegrin counterpart Boro Vucin.
(MIA, RTRS, Fena - 21/12/06)
